ComicInfo.Summary: The second issue of the three-part "Superbabes" trilogy leads of with a 24-page barnburner of a conclusion to last issue's "Out of The Past" Femforce lead story, as the circe 1955 team of Miss Victory, She-Cat, Rio Rita, Blue Bulleteer and Blonde Bomber start out as the helpless captives of the villainess Rathschilde. When it becomes obvious that mere super-powers won't defeat their suddenly-savage opponent, brains, bravery and teamwork must save the day. And wait'll you see who was REALLY behind this time-twisted plot all along. Written by Mark & Stephanie Heike, penciled by Jeff Austin, with inks by Mark, Jeff & Steph. Then, the gorgeous gal-character guest-stories continue, with the dark-alley mystery of Femme Noir, written by veteran comics pro Chris Mills, drawn by all-time great Joe Staton, and inked by talented new embellisher Horatio Ottolini. The mysterious blonde distaff detective (and star of Chris Mills' supernaturalcrime.com website) trades pot-shots with gangsters, thugs and various outrageous characters in a stolen-artifact switcheroo called "The Dingus". Mauricio Hunt's teen heroine Kinetics ( you may remember her cameos in Femforce #99 & 100 ) gets a feature story of her own, as the pert and perky super-powered alien must defeat an awesome rock monster while "Going To The Movies", as illustrated by Adriano Vicente Santos. All this plus pin-ups , too!! Color cover (by Mark & Stephanie Heike) with black & white interoirs, 44 pages, standard comic book size.
ComicInfo.Title: Going to the Movies; The Dingus; Out of the Past!: Part 2
